**Company Profile: J.B. Hunt Transport Services, Inc.**

As of the 2024 Fortune ranking, J.B. Hunt Transport Services, Inc. holds the 316th position, a notable decrease from its previous year's standing. With its headquarters located in Lowell, Arkansas, the company operates in the transportation sector, specifically focusing on trucking and truck leasing services.

Founded by Johnnie Bryan Hunt in 1961, J.B. Hunt Transport Services has evolved into a leading player in the industry. However, its founder is no longer at the helm; Shelley Simpson currently serves as the company's Chief Executive Officer. Notably, the company does not have a female CEO, which is a common trait among many Fortune-ranked companies.

In terms of employment, J.B. Hunt Transport Services boasts a substantial workforce of 34,718 employees. Despite this, the company experienced a decline in job growth in the recent year. This downturn is reflective of the challenges faced by the industry as a whole.

The company's financial performance, as reflected in the 2024 Fortune ranking, reveals a mix of both positive and negative trends. J.B. Hunt Transport Services' revenues reached $12.8 billion, a decrease of 13.4 percent from the previous year. This decline had a ripple effect on the company's profits, which also fell by 24.9 percent to $728.3 million. The company's market value, as of March 28, 2024, stood at $20.6 billion, while its assets totaled $8.5 billion.

J.B. Hunt Transport Services has managed to maintain its position as a profitable entity, despite the challenges it faced in the recent year. However, its ranking decline of 36 positions in the Fortune 1000 list is a cause for concern. This downturn may be attributed to the company's inability to adapt to the changing market dynamics and increasing competition in the transportation sector.

On a more positive note, J.B. Hunt Transport Services has been recognized as one of the World's Most Admired Companies, a testament to its commitment to excellence and customer satisfaction. The company's website, accessible at [https://www.jbhunt.com](https://www.jbhunt.com), provides an overview of its services and operations.

As a publicly traded company, J.B. Hunt Transport Services, Inc. is subject to the scrutiny of investors and stakeholders. Its market value, updated as of June 4, 2024, remains at $20.6 billion. Despite the challenges it faces, the company remains a key player in the transportation sector, with a rich history and a strong presence in the market.